		 		<p class = "cent_text big_print"><strong>Childhood</strong></p> 
		  		<p>During his childhood, Darrell Cheng was constantly neglected by his parents due to being the younger

				child. This constant neglect during his childhood years prompted Darrell to train intensively in order to one

				day surpass his brother, Bryce. As the other half of the "Twin Dragons," Darrell went to the University of

				Washington Academy for Young Scholars in order to gain the skills necessary to survive in a high-stakes business environment.</p>
				<p class = "cent_text big_print"><strong>Rice to Greatness</strong></p> 
				<p>After graduating from the University of Washington Academy for Young Scholars, Cheng

				established a strong foothold in the entertainment business by constructing a slew of high-end night

				clubs in government-designated brownfields, lands previously considered "lost" due to excessive human

				abuse. By doing so, Cheng won the Nobel Peace Prize in 2014 for the effective reclamation of

				brownfields. In addition, Darrell was able to establish a monopoly in the entertainment business by

				suing other companies on grounds of excessive contamination of the environment. As a result, the company,

				"Cheng Consolidated Entertainment Facilities" was born.</p>
				<p class = "cent_text big_print"><strong>Enlightenment and Future Investment in Philanthropy</strong></p>
				<p>At the epitome of his success, Cheng was described

				as an ignorant and inconsiderate playboy. However, this all changed when Darrell's yacht, the Verdant

				Legacy, capsized during a storm. Cheng later spent five months on the distant island of Lien Choy. Not

				much is known about his five month excursion, but Darrell proclaimed himself a changed man after

				he was rescued by Indonesian fisherman. In order to atone for his past actions as the playboy leach of the

				Cheng Family, Darrell co-founded the Cheng foundation with his older brother, Bryce.</p>
